sentences: An Pierlé (born An Miel Mia Pierlé on 13 December 1974) is a Belgian pianist and singer-songwriter.
Shortly after she became known to a moderately wide audience in 1996 when she entered Humo's Rock Rally with a tape of her own version of Gary Numan's Are 'Friends' Electric?.
In 1998 she signed a record deal with Warner Music Benelux.
The extra acoustic piano parts were done in the spring of 1999.
In 2002 An Pierlé released her second record, Helium Sunset.
Singles & Rarities + Live in Brussels, Paris & Hamburg (2008)Singles

Most of the album was recorded on electric piano in the winter of 1998 and 1999 in the attic of a theatre in Ghent (in some songs, with high quality audio equipment, very faint background car noises can be heard).
In her third year there she made a solo programme with songs of her own, alone at the piano.

After this, Pierlé toured for two years with a theatre group, and starred in a Belgium television series (Moeder, waarom leven wij?), gave a few solo performances and collaborated with DAAU on their song "Broken", where she sings all of the vocals.
The extra acoustic piano parts were done in the spring of 1999.
In 2002 An Pierlé released her second record, Helium Sunset.
Following the release of Helium Sunset was a live album named Live Jetset with Orchestra, an album with back up from a full orchestra.

This album was apparently very limited in release numbers and sold out pretty quickly.2005 saw a new release of Helium Sunset, complete with a new cover featuring An Pierlé (unlike the first releases).
Pierlé and band released the album An Pierlé & White Velvet in early May 2006.
Pierlé and the band are now also performing under the same name.
As of late April 2006, the first single named "How Does It Feel?" was already available for download in online stores, including two studio live covers.
